	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If you have a converter that's female A/V audio to male eighth inch (like headphones) like this:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.vgmusic.com/faq/gallery/adapters/a-f_StereoRCA-m_8thHP.jpg">http://www.vgmusic.com/faq/gallery/adap ... _8thHP.jpg</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Then I would just recommend plugging the NES in with an A/V cable, but put the sound cables into the converter and hook it up to your computer (if it has a microphone or line-in input). Then just record the audio coming in with something like Windows Movie Maker.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


